				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 07 Feb 2020 14:07:14 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TacticalShrubbery</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5675422</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>“Anomalous phone calls generated at this location cause human subjects who answer them to be treated as though they are &quot;at work&quot;.”</p> <p>“Regardless of whether the subject answers the call or agrees to the request, they will become affected by SCP-3831.”</p> <p>I might be reading it wrong, but this looks like a discrepancy in how the SCP works. Do they have to answer the call or not?</p> <p>Also, love the article. Interesting concept that made me want to know more. And that note at the end, that hit really well. Changed my whole perspective on the thing. Well done!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
